In a speech at the National Defense University, Vice President Mike Pence announced plans to establish a new branch of the United States Armed Forces called the United States Space Force. Pence stated that the creation of a Space Force is necessary to ensure American dominance in space and protect national security interests. He outlined several steps that the administration will take to establish the Space Force, including the creation of a new unified combatant command called the United States Space Command and the establishment of a new joint organization called the Space Development Agency. Pence also emphasized the need for centralized leadership and accountability in space operations and called on Congress to pass legislation to establish the Space Force.